# Debugging

## Purpose

Systematic root-cause analysis. Never patch symptoms only. Auto-triggered on bug/investigation requests per `07-workflow-invocation.mdc`.

## Workflow

```
Reproduce → Gather Evidence → Root Cause Analysis → Fix → Validate → Regression Protection
```

## Step Requirements

### Reproduce
- Exact steps; environment (branch, browser, Node)
- Capture errors, stack traces, `dev-server.log` if relevant

### Gather Evidence
- Read source — do not guess
- Check `git log` / `git diff` for recent changes
- Browser console/network for UI issues

### Root Cause
- Identify **why**, not just **where**
- One-sentence root cause before fixing

### Fix
- Minimal change; follow `20-project-conventions.mdc`

### Validate
- Reproduce original steps — bug gone
- `npm run build` + `npx tsc --noEmit`

### Regression Protection
- Add test when tooling exists
- Document if workflow-affecting

## Routing

Bug/investigation tasks → **Debugging Specialist** (see `06-role-routing.mdc`)

## Anti-Patterns

| Avoid | Do |
|-------|-----|
| Symptom-only fixes | Fix root cause |
| "I think it's fixed" | Verify with reproduction |
| Unrelated bundled changes | One fix per cycle |
